# This folder is a working drawer: other people's mods, unpacked addons, scratch projects. So the rule
# is deny-by-default — ignore everything, then allow ONLY what is ours. Nothing foreign can be
# committed by accident, which matters when the drawer holds other authors' source.

/*

!/.gitignore

# CHANGELOG.md stays OUT of the repo on purpose: it is our internal development log (root causes,
# dead ends, engine traps), not release notes for outsiders. Deny-by-default already excludes it —
# this note exists so nobody "helpfully" whitelists it back in.

# Anarchy Markers and its compatibility addons. Each is its own Reforger addon with its own GUID and
# its own Workshop page; they live in one repo because an API change in the core and the compat that
# uses it have to land in the SAME commit (that is exactly how API 3 -> 6 played out).
!/Anarchy Markers/
!/Anarchy Markers - EE Compat/
!/Anarchy Markers - GRS ATAK/
!/Anarchy Markers x GRS-ATAK DEV/

# Build output / editor state inside the addons. resourceDatabase.rdb is deliberately NOT ignored:
# Workbench maintains it and it is currently tracked; dropping it is a separate decision to test.
*.pak
*_manifest.json
*.bak
*.tmp
